bilingual.source: There is a clock on the wall.
The clock on the wall is broken.

bilingual.target: 她把时钟设定在早上7点。

bilingual.source: Look at the clock to check the time.
The clock in the kitchen is very old.

bilingual.target: 时钟的指针顺时针方向移动。

bilingual.source: We should hang the clock on the wall.
bilingual.target: 我们应该把时钟挂在墙上。

bilingual.source: The clock repeats its chime every hour.
bilingual.target: 时钟每小时重复敲响一次。

bilingual.source: The cog in the clock needs to be replaced.
bilingual.target: 时钟里的齿轮需要更换。

list.abstract: clock是C/C++中的计时函数，而与其相关的数据类型是clock_t。这个函数返回从“开启这个程序进程”到“程序中调用clock()函数”时之间的CPU时钟计时单元（clock tick）数，在MSDN中称之为挂钟时间（wal-clock）；若挂钟时间不可取，则返回-1。
clock是一个英语单词，可以用作名词和动词，可以翻译为钟、时钟，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: Unfortunately, your body's internal clock isn't really easy to change.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但很可惜，体内的生理时钟不是那么容易改变。

yingyinNormal.en: According to the world's worst cuckoo clock, it's 2:00.
yingyinNormal.zh: 史上最烂的布谷鸟报时钟刚说 两点了。

yingyinNormal.en: Let me see what I've got in a van. One grand clock. It's a bit big.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看看我的货车里有什么。一个时钟。看上去有点太大了。

yingyinNormal.en: Let me see what I've got in a van. One grand clock. It's a bit big.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看看我的货车里有什么。一个时钟。看上去有点太大了。

yingyinNormal.en: What? Come on, I mean it's not like I'm asking for this girly clock or anything, which, by the way, I also think is very cool.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？好啦，我又不是要这个美女时钟或什么的，但我觉得这个也很酷。

yingyinNormal.en: This may be difficult for you to hear, but you are a hand on a clock, understand? We set you, you move forward. We reset you, you move again. And that represents the entirety of your function here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这你听起来可能很费解，但你就是时钟上的指针，我们给你上了发条，你就开始转动，再上一次发条，你又开始转动，你的作用就体现在此。

yingyinNormal.en: My goodness, five o'clock already.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的天啊，已经五点钟了。

yingyinNormal.en: My goodness, five o'clock already.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的天啊，已经五点钟了。

yingyinNormal.en: It's one o'clock. They're late as usual.
yingyinNormal.zh: 已经一点钟了。他们迟到了就和以前一样。

yingyinNormal.en: What time is it now? Ten o'clock. Hurray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么现在是几点呢？十点啦。太好了！

yingyinNormal.en: The stable clock's fast. We ought to get back.
yingyinNormal.zh: 马厩的钟快了，我们得走了。

yingyinNormal.en: Hoho, we've plenty of time. It's only eleven o'clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 喔喔，我们还有很多时间。现在才11点。

yingyinNormal.en: Eight o'clock, Wednesday night. I called Patti myself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 周三晚上八点，我亲自和帕特打招呼。

yingyinNormal.en: Hang on. Okay. Here's what we're gonna do. Chess clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等一下，有了，我们接下来这么干，赛棋钟。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy Pig is winding up the cuckoo clock. There. Daddy Pig sets the clock to the right time. It is nearly 9 o'clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸重新给钟上了一下发条。好了。猪爸爸给钟重新调了时间。现在已经快九点了。

yingyinNormal.en: The actor playing Mac couldn't do it, they needed to see you at 2 o'clock. What? It's 6 o'clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要演麦克的演员不能演，他们要你2点过去。什么？明明是6点。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. We've got a group of cool girls at 2 o'clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 两点钟方向有一群酷女生。

yingyinNormal.en: What is all of this? I got it. Good. Tired. Four o'clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是怎么回事？我来搞定。很好，累，四点。

yingyinNormal.en: I got fired, Mrs. Underwood. I'm not on the clock anymore.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我被解雇了，安德伍德夫人， 我不再受雇了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh dear. Let's see if we can mend it. The old cuckoo clock.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢糟糕。我们来看看能不能修好。那个旧的布谷鸟钟。

examination_example.sentence: You wish that you could turn back the <highlight>clock</highlight> and start over.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你希望能时光倒流，重新开始。

examination_example.sentence: Parkrun is not a race but a time trial: Your only competitor is the <highlight>clock</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Parkrun不是竞赛，而是计时赛：你唯一的竞争对手是时间。

examination_example.sentence: For example, the Long Now Foundation has as its flagship project a mechanical <highlight>clock</highlight> that is designed to still be marking time thousands of years hence.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，恒今基金会将一个机械时钟作为其旗舰项目，其目的是在数千年后仍然可以计时。

examination_example.sentence: But a boost in the storage capacity of batteries is making their ability to keep power flowing around the <highlight>clock</highlight> more likely.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是，电池容量的提升使其更更有能夜以继日地保持供电。

examination_example.sentence: The second day I set two <highlight>clocks</highlight>, one on my night table, and one out in the hallway.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第二天，我设置了两个时钟，一个在我的床头柜上，一个在走廊上。

examination_example.sentence: If the rivers run faster in the future on average, the <highlight>clock</highlight> will get ahead of standard time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果未来的河流平均流速加快，时钟就会比标准时间走得快。

examination_example.sentence: Why did the author place an alarm <highlight>clock</highlight> in the hallway?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作者为什么要把闹钟放在走廊里？

examination_example.sentence: Some people seem willing to work around the <highlight>clock</highlight> in their narrow specialty.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有些人似乎愿意在他们狭窄的专业领域里夜以继日地工作。

examination_example.sentence: Globally, a third of Sumatran cubs in zoos don't make it to adulthood, so I decided to give them round-the-<highlight>clock</highlight> care at home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在全球范围内，动物园里有三分之一的苏门答腊幼虎无法活到成年，所以我决定在家里全天候照料它们。
